><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131409344,imgsize-233588.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Unruly passenger disrupts United Airlines flight bound for Minneapolis, plane seeks FBI's help]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131408762.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/unruly-passenger-disrupts-united-airlines-flight-bound-for-minneapolis-plane-seeks-fbis-help/articleshow/131408762.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/unruly-passenger-disrupts-united-airlines-flight-bound-for-minneapolis-plane-seeks-fbis-help/articleshow/131408762.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-30T17:15:35+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131408804,imgsize-41264.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Truck carrying Afghan refugees from Pakistan overturns, killing 22]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131408364.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A tragic road accident in eastern Afghanistan claimed at least 22 lives, including 10 children and five women, as a truck carrying returning refugees overturned. Officials reported around 36 others injured. The incident, attributed to the driver reportedly falling asleep, highlights the perilous journeys of Afghans returning from Pakistan and Iran amidst increased expulsions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/journey-home-ends-in-tragedy-truck-carrying-afghan-refugees-from-pakistan-overturns-killing-22/articleshow/131408364.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/journey-home-ends-in-tragedy-truck-carrying-afghan-refugees-from-pakistan-overturns-killing-22/articleshow/131408364.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-30T16:51:10+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131408445,imgsize-948908.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pakistan hires US lobbying firm to advance strategic interests in Washington amid Iran war diplomacy push]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131408327.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Pakistan has hired a US lobbying firm, Ervin Graves Strategy Group, for a two-year contract worth $50,000 monthly. The firm will advocate for Pakistan's diplomatic, economic, and strategic interests in Washington, engaging with Congress, the executive branch, and policy institutions. This initiative aims to bolster Pakistan's standing as a US ally and its role in regional diplomacy.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-hires-us-lobbying-firm-to-advance-strategic-interests-in-washington-amid-iran-war-diplomacy-push/articleshow/131408327.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-hires-us-lobbying-firm-to-advance-strategic-interests-in-washington-amid-iran-war-diplomacy-push/articleshow/131408327.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-30T16:48:45+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131408402,imgsize-408658.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UK man, 68, dies rescuing granddaughter after family swept out to sea in Cornwall]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131407948.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/uk-man-68-dies-rescuing-granddaughter-after-family-swept-out-to-sea-in-cornwall/articleshow/131407948.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/uk-man-68-dies-rescuing-granddaughter-after-family-swept-out-to-sea-in-cornwall/articleshow/131407948.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-30T16:23:13+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131408024,imgsize-386881.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Iran missile strike at Kuwait base damages US drones, injures Americans: Report]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131407551.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[An Iranian missile struck Ali Al Salem Air Base in Kuwait. The attack damaged two US MQ-9 Reaper drones, with one destroyed and another severely damaged. Several American personnel sustained minor injuries. Kuwaiti air defenses intercepted the missile, but debris fell onto the base.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/iran-missile-strike-at-kuwait-base-damages-us-drones-injures-americans-report/articleshow/131407551.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/iran-missile-strike-at-kuwait-base-damages-us-drones-injures-americans-report/articleshow/131407551.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-30T15:49:05+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131407566,imgsize-471874.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Iran likey used Chinese-made missile to down US F-15: Reports]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131407066.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A US F-15E Strike Eagle was reportedly shot down over Iran by a Chinese-made shoulder-launched missile, marking a significant escalation. While US officials investigate, China denies providing recent military support, though past assistance and potential radar technology transfers are noted. The incident complicates ongoing US-China relations amid peace negotiations.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/iran-likey-used-chinese-made-missile-to-down-us-f-15-reports/articleshow/131407066.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/iran-likey-used-chinese-made-missile-to-down-us-f-15-reports/articleshow/131407066.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-30T15:08:24+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131407105,imgsize-1040708.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meet the Moon Trees: Apollo 14 astronaut carried hundreds of tree seeds around the Moon in 1971 and now they are flourishing across America]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131395224.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/meet-the-moon-trees-apollo-14-astronaut-carried-hundreds-of-tree-seeds-around-the-moon-in-1971-and-now-they-are-flourishing-across-america/articleshow/131395224.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/meet-the-moon-trees-apollo-14-astronaut-carried-hundreds-of-tree-seeds-around-the-moon-in-1971-and-now-they-are-flourishing-across-america/articleshow/131395224.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-29T22:43:03+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https:/